cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of training neural networks to classify images without relying on protected concepts such as gender or race. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and neural networks (cs.NE). However, given that the paper focuses on developing a method for training agnostic models, which is a core problem in machine learning, we believe that cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant because they deal with related topics such as image classification, domain adaptation, and fairness in machine learning.
